                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/5311: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-12T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 12, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 12—10:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>54. Department’s 36, November 7, 4 p.m. Negotiations between director Bulgarian
                    public debt and Greek Government resulted yesterday in temporary agreement to
                    suspend mutual payments, from Bulgaria to Greece under head of reparations, and
                    from Greece to Bulgaria under Kafandaris-Molloff agreement during present
                    moratorium.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
